<p><br />
<b>Dr. Norman Vincent Peale</b> (May 31, 1898&#160;– December 24, 1993) was a <a href="/wiki/Protestant" title="Protestant" class="mw-redirect">Protestant</a> <a href="/wiki/Preacher" title="Preacher">preacher</a> and <a href="/wiki/Author" title="Author">author</a> (most notably of <i>The Power of Positive Thinking</i>) and a progenitor of the theory of "<a href="/wiki/Positive_thinking" title="Positive thinking" class="mw-redirect">positive thinking</a>".</p>
